definition :
-->used to create object in java.
-->special type of method which has same name as class name
-->If there is no any user defined constructor in class then java provides default constructor to create object.
--> Types :
        1> Default Constructor:
            use to create objects and set default value to it.
                syntax:
                    class_name(){
                    //set default values to object
                    }
        2>Parameterized Constructor:
            used to create object and set dynamic values to it.

            syntax:
                class_name(arg_1,arg_2,....arg_n){
                    //set dynamic values
                    }

****> constructor return values?
        yes , objects of classes...
        it implicitly returns the object



'this' keyword :
    -->represents current object
    -->we can call
        -->instance variables
        -->instance methods
        -->instance constructors
        using 'this'  keyword





